      <title>Link: Distributed Ruby Guide</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href="http://whytheluckystiff.net/"&gt;_why&lt;/a&gt;&amp;#8217;s recent &lt;a href="http://redhanded.hobix.com/cult/drbRenaissance.html"&gt;announcement&lt;/a&gt; of the Drb Renaissance, I figured it was time to finally get my feet wet and learn about using &lt;a href="http://www.ruby-doc.org/stdlib/libdoc/drb/rdoc/index.html"&gt;Distributed Ruby&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fortunately, &lt;a href="http://www.chadfowler.com/"&gt;Chad Fowler&lt;/a&gt; author of the fantastic &lt;a href="http://pragmaticprogrammer.com/titles/fr_rr/index.html"&gt;Rails Recipes&lt;/a&gt;,  has done my work for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Go check out his &lt;a href="http://www.chadfowler.com/ruby/drb.html"&gt;guide&lt;/a&gt; for an excellent quick read on the essentials of Drb.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
